19:25.790 --> 19:28.000
ROB: Do you recognize
this man?

19:28.125 --> 19:30.169
Never seen him
around the estate?

19:32.046 --> 19:33.047
You sure?

19:34.757 --> 19:36.050
I'm sure.

19:40.971 --> 19:42.098
Jess.

19:42.223 --> 19:44.600
Stop, you're going
to get sick.

19:45.726 --> 19:47.144
ROB: Rosalind.

19:47.269 --> 19:51.691
You went away for a few days
in May to stay with a friend.

19:51.816 --> 19:52.942
Is that right?

19:54.235 --> 19:55.903
Simone Cameron mentioned it.

19:56.862 --> 19:58.072
Who was the friend?

19:58.197 --> 19:59.824
Just a girl
| used to know in school.

20:01.409 --> 20:03.786
Rosalind, if the friend
is a boy, you can say.

20:03.911 --> 20:05.204
A boy?

20:05.329 --> 20:06.706
Or a man.

20:07.957 --> 20:09.250
When | look like this?

20:10.960 --> 20:13.003
It was just a girl
| used to know in school.

20:15.172 --> 20:16.590
I'm sorry.

20:16.716 --> 20:18.050
| have to get
the tea ready.

20:18.175 --> 20:19.719
Jess, come on.

20:19.844 --> 20:21.887
Look, | got you something.

20:22.012 --> 20:23.681
Are you all right
about taking this?

20:25.349 --> 20:27.268
My number's in it.
It's all paid for.

20:31.772 --> 20:33.357
Now, you ring me anytime.

20:33.816 --> 20:35.401
Day or night.

20:35.526 --> 20:38.112
If you remember something, if
you're not sure about something,

20:38.237 --> 20:40.698
if you want to talk,
if you need help.

20:42.324 --> 20:43.659
Okay?

20:51.333 --> 20:52.334
Jess?

21:03.721 --> 21:05.139
BOYLE: You must have
a theory, Ms. Rowan.

21:05.264 --> 21:06.766
ALICIA: | do.

21:06.891 --> 21:10.227
Katy Devlin was murdered
by someone who knows this estate

21:10.352 --> 21:12.104
and knows those woods.

21:12.229 --> 21:14.231
This man that was seen
at the dig,

21:14.356 --> 21:16.776
this man they say
they're looking for,

21:17.735 --> 21:19.069
| think it's Adam.

21:19.195 --> 21:21.405
He walked out of those
woods without a mark on him.

21:21.530 --> 21:24.033
And he knows what happened
to Jamie and Peter.

21:24.158 --> 21:25.826
Adam was a child himself.

21:25.951 --> 21:29.163
We all know children can
be brutal to each other.

21:29.288 --> 21:31.290
And Adam
is a grown man now.

21:31.415 --> 21:35.419
A grown man who knows this
estate and knows those woods.

21:36.378 --> 21:38.005
Look for him.

21:38.130 --> 21:40.841
Ask him where he was
the night Katy was killed.

21:40.966 --> 21:43.803
Ask him what happened to
my daughter and her friend.

21:44.178 --> 21:45.429
Ask Adam.

21:52.061 --> 21:53.312
[ BREATHES HEAVILY ]

22:19.547 --> 22:21.131
CATHAL: You haven't got shit.

22:26.804 --> 22:28.430
[ GIRL PANTING ]

22:46.115 --> 22:47.366
[ DOG BARKING ]

23:00.796 --> 23:02.923
YOUNG ROB:
Peter, where are you?

23:03.591 --> 23:05.843
Peter, Jamie.

23:10.055 --> 23:11.265
[ PANTING ]

23:34.580 --> 23:36.373
There's no blood
in the house.

23:38.167 --> 23:40.085
This tree is in the grounds.

23:40.210 --> 23:43.047
That's where the blood is.
Washed away.

23:43.172 --> 23:46.008
Not just from rain, but someone
went out with detergent.

23:46.133 --> 23:48.385
Soapy runoff in the tree
roots and undergrowth.

23:48.510 --> 23:49.845
No weapon.

23:50.930 --> 23:51.972
That's where
she was stabbed.

23:53.098 --> 23:54.600
Great work, O'Neill.

23:54.725 --> 23:56.977
Wel'll, uh...
We'll take it from here.

24:06.904 --> 24:07.947
[ DOOR OPENS ]

24:08.072 --> 24:10.491
Soapy runoff
at the roots.

24:10.616 --> 24:12.409
- Good little housekeepers.
-[ DOOR CLOSES ]

24:12.534 --> 24:13.619
It's not good enough.

24:14.954 --> 24:15.955
One second.

24:20.250 --> 24:21.251
CASSIE: Sam?

24:24.338 --> 24:25.339
Look...

24:26.632 --> 24:28.258
| just want
to clear the air.

24:29.635 --> 24:30.719
Things didn't work out
between us,

24:30.844 --> 24:33.347
- but let's be professional...
- Fuck you, Cassie.

24:36.976 --> 24:39.228
Jesus Christ.
Well, | tried.

24:39.353 --> 24:40.604
And fuck Rob, too.

24:40.729 --> 24:42.272
Not that it's done
you much good.

24:42.940 --> 24:43.983
Has it?

24:46.652 --> 24:48.028
How did you...

24:49.363 --> 24:50.906
I've got to carry on
working with him.

24:51.031 --> 24:52.408
Fuck you very much.

24:59.039 --> 25:00.082
[ DOOR OPENS ]

25:01.458 --> 25:02.626
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

25:10.509 --> 25:12.052
[ GULLS SQUAWKING ]

25:54.470 --> 25:55.971
| got your prescription.

25:58.098 --> 26:00.142
And whose fault is it
| have to take them?

26:03.228 --> 26:04.646
[ EXHALING ]

26:14.114 --> 26:15.199
BOYLE: Detective.

26:15.324 --> 26:16.450
Did you see
my front page?

26:16.575 --> 26:17.993
Wondering if you had
any comment.

26:18.118 --> 26:19.661
Alicia Rowan is
a vulnerable woman.

26:19.787 --> 26:20.829
You're exploiting
her grief.

26:20.954 --> 26:23.540
You say exploiting, | say
speaking truth to power.

26:23.665 --> 26:26.293
And it's a good question.
Where is Adam?

26:26.418 --> 26:28.295
He changed his name.
We're tracing him.

26:28.420 --> 26:30.422
Anything else to say
to reassure my readers?

26:30.547 --> 26:32.132
Yeah, sure.

26:32.257 --> 26:34.426
Fuck off and stop trying
to derail my investigation.

26:34.551 --> 26:37.012
What investigation?
You don't have a suspect.

26:37.137 --> 26:39.598
And until you do, I'l
keep asking about Adam.

26:39.723 --> 26:41.683
There's a story here.
| know it.

26:42.476 --> 26:43.602
Find Adam.

26:43.727 --> 26:45.104
He could be your man.

27:02.788 --> 27:04.206
[ RUFFLING ]

27:05.624 --> 27:06.750
Who's there?

27:09.128 --> 27:10.170
[ ROSALIND SCREAMS |

27:10.295 --> 27:11.421
Get out!

27:13.298 --> 27:14.466
Get out!

27:15.259 --> 27:16.260
Mummy!

27:20.514 --> 27:21.515
Please.

27:24.184 --> 27:26.103
| never wanted you.

27:36.321 --> 27:37.489
[ PANTING ]

27:40.742 --> 27:41.910
Apart from Daniel March,

27:42.035 --> 27:44.163
not one of them with a
history of violence.

27:44.580 --> 27:45.831
Until now.

27:46.707 --> 27:49.334
Raphael Lahiri.
Rafe.

27:49.459 --> 27:51.712
Family owns hotels.
They're loaded.

27:51.837 --> 27:53.630
He gets an allowance.

27:53.755 --> 27:55.632
Spunked a fortune
on cocaine.

27:55.757 --> 27:58.093
Clean now,
thanks to...

27:58.218 --> 27:59.178
Daniel March.

27:59.553 --> 28:00.846
Justin Mannering.

28:01.138 --> 28:03.724
Parents divorced, spends
his childhood pinballing

28:03.849 --> 28:05.726
between people
who hate each other.

28:05.851 --> 28:08.187
They both remarry
and get new families.

28:08.312 --> 28:10.689
He's on his own until this
new family comes along.

28:10.814 --> 28:11.899
Courtesy of...

28:14.359 --> 28:15.527
Abigail Stone.

28:15.652 --> 28:17.112
She's been the subject
of care orders

28:17.237 --> 28:18.572
since she popped
out of the womb.

28:18.697 --> 28:19.907
Mother's fucking insane.

28:20.032 --> 28:21.491
Her whole life
has been chaos.

28:21.617 --> 28:22.743
But look at her.

28:22.868 --> 28:25.662
Smart as a whip,
she works and works.

28:25.787 --> 28:29.249
Gets herself a scholarship
to Trinity, and a home.

28:29.374 --> 28:30.584
Thanks to...

28:31.418 --> 28:32.419
Daniel March.

28:32.669 --> 28:34.630
She'll fight hard.

28:34.755 --> 28:36.757
She's the one
who scares me.

28:36.882 --> 28:37.883
Reminds me of that
picture of you

28:38.008 --> 28:39.885
and Sammy Boy
you've got in your flat.

28:40.010 --> 28:42.262
She looks at him
the way he looked at you.

28:43.472 --> 28:44.681
Proper love.

28:45.933 --> 28:48.143
Whatever that is.

28:48.268 --> 28:50.604
But Daniel's not looking at
her. He's looking at Lexie.

28:51.855 --> 28:53.732
So she should scare you.

29:04.576 --> 29:05.869
DAMIEN:
It's the detective, Mum.

29:05.994 --> 29:09.164
The one for Katy.
The one I've been helping.

29:09.289 --> 29:11.375
MOTHER:
Well, go and help him then.

29:11.500 --> 29:13.543
[ MOTHER CONTINUES
INDISTINCTLY ]

29:30.310 --> 29:31.353
[ SIGHS ]

29:31.478 --> 29:32.479
DAMIEN: Detective Reilly.

29:32.896 --> 29:35.315
- Do you want a coffee?
- | need you to come with me.

29:35.440 --> 29:37.150
[ STUTTERS ]I can't.

29:37.276 --> 29:38.902
The neighbor who sits
with Mum is out, and...

29:39.027 --> 29:40.696
There's a female garda outside.

29:40.821 --> 29:42.489
I'll let her in, she can meet
your mum and then we can go.

29:43.532 --> 29:44.533
Okay.

29:48.495 --> 29:49.746
[ TATTOO MACHINE BUZZING ]

30:00.465 --> 30:01.925
- [ BREATHES DEEPLY ]
- [ BUZZING CONTINUES ]

30:29.661 --> 30:31.455
[ SCISSORS SNIPPING ]

30:48.930 --> 30:51.391
Jesus. That's actually quite
alarming. Say something.

30:51.516 --> 30:55.437
[ IMPERSONATING LEXIE ]
We're all going to die.

30:55.562 --> 30:58.565
Oh, God, Lexie, what
happened? Who did it?

30:58.690 --> 31:01.693
| don't know.
| don't remember.

31:02.819 --> 31:05.030
| just want to come home.

31:05.155 --> 31:07.908
| want to get out of this
fucking hospital and come home.

31:08.033 --> 31:10.702
Heartbreaking.
I'm having emotions.

31:10.827 --> 31:12.454
[ LAUGHING |

31:14.039 --> 31:16.541
I'm going to have to leave
the dig permanently.

31:16.666 --> 31:18.752
Mum needs me full time.

31:18.877 --> 31:20.087
I'm going to
really miss it.

31:20.212 --> 31:21.963
| need you to show me where you
saw this man in the tracksuit,

31:22.089 --> 31:23.715
where he was standing.

31:23.840 --> 31:24.966
- I'm not sure if
| can remember...

31:25.092 --> 31:25.967
- Close enough will do.

31:28.470 --> 31:30.889
[ BIRDS CHIRPING ]

31:36.686 --> 31:38.688
| was...
| was round about here.

31:38.814 --> 31:40.440
And he was over there.

31:40.774 --> 31:42.567
Okay.

31:42.692 --> 31:45.112
Now, turn away and don't
look around until | tell you.

32:12.055 --> 32:13.682
- Close your eyes.
- What?

32:14.641 --> 32:15.892
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

32:19.604 --> 32:20.730
Open.

32:22.149 --> 32:23.692
That's the man you saw.

32:24.568 --> 32:25.569
I'm not sure.

32:25.694 --> 32:27.571
Damien, you need
to stop pissing about.

32:28.071 --> 32:30.031
Look, think.

32:30.157 --> 32:31.992
- This is the man you saw.
-[ SOBS ]

32:32.117 --> 32:33.410
I've been doing nothing
but looking

32:33.618 --> 32:34.744
and thinking, and I'm not sure.

32:34.870 --> 32:36.121
It was summer. More leaf cover,

32:36.329 --> 32:37.747
his face would have
been in shadow.

32:37.873 --> 32:39.374
DAMIEN: You want me to say
it's him, but | can't!

32:39.499 --> 32:41.084
| can't if I'm not sure,
and I'm not! I'm not!

32:41.209 --> 32:42.711
MARK: That's enough.

32:44.004 --> 32:45.172
It's enough.

32:48.800 --> 32:49.676
Fine. I'll...
I'll take him home.

32:49.801 --> 32:52.429
No, no. I'll take him home.
Go on, Damien.

32:56.725 --> 32:59.102
Even | know that
this is way out of line.

32:59.227 --> 33:00.896
And if | know it, then
that means you do, too.

33:04.608 --> 33:06.026
Back to work.

33:06.151 --> 33:07.527
[ CELL PHONE RINGING ]

33:11.114 --> 33:12.491
Rosalind.

33:15.160 --> 33:16.578
I'm on my way.

33:50.987 --> 33:52.155
Rosalind?

33:52.697 --> 33:54.241
Hi!

33:54.366 --> 33:57.244
| got you a juice
because you're on duty.

33:57.369 --> 34:00.121
But, do you want
peanuts or anything?

34:00.247 --> 34:01.790
No, I'm all good,
thanks.

34:16.221 --> 34:17.973
Has something happened,
Rosalind?

34:19.056 --> 34:20.976
No, nothing.

34:22.018 --> 34:24.563
Nothing out of the ordinary,
anyway.

34:27.190 --> 34:30.694
Has something happened
that used to be ordinary?

34:31.777 --> 34:32.946
[ SNORTS ]

34:34.947 --> 34:36.324
[ MAN COUGHS |

34:47.627 --> 34:48.628
Rosalind.

34:49.754 --> 34:51.172
Christ.

34:51.840 --> 34:53.007
No.

34:53.132 --> 34:54.551
No. Absolutely not.

35:02.726 --> 35:06.146
| thought that's why
you asked me about boyfriends,

35:07.355 --> 35:09.649
why you gave me the phone.

35:11.735 --> 35:13.194
| get everything wrong.

35:14.904 --> 35:16.656
I'm sorry.

35:16.781 --> 35:18.700
I'm... I'm so sorry.

35:22.912 --> 35:24.664
| don't know
what I'm doing.

35:26.082 --> 35:29.210
L... 1 don't know who...

35:29.336 --> 35:30.587
| don't know who | am.

35:31.921 --> 35:33.214
Not...

35:33.923 --> 35:35.342
Not without Katy.

35:36.092 --> 35:37.344
[ SOBBING ]

35:37.469 --> 35:39.929
| just miss her
so much...

35:42.098 --> 35:44.017
| think I'm going mad
with this.

35:44.142 --> 35:48.021
Just... Just left behind
like this,

35:48.146 --> 35:50.982
and no one understands,
no one...

35:51.107 --> 35:52.067
| understand.

35:52.275 --> 35:53.318
No!

35:53.443 --> 35:54.819
You don't.

35:54.944 --> 35:57.614
You don't.
No one does.

35:57.739 --> 35:59.616
I'm another one
that got left behind.

35:59.991 --> 36:01.034
Just like you.

36:02.911 --> 36:06.373
My friend disappeared.

36:07.916 --> 36:11.836
My best friend.
One day just vanished.

36:12.629 --> 36:15.924
He was just gone.
And | was lost.

36:18.134 --> 36:21.179
Everything turned on its head.
Nothing made sense.

36:23.390 --> 36:24.933
Left behind.

36:26.976 --> 36:29.312
So | do understand.
| really do.

36:32.399 --> 36:34.818
Is that why you wanted
to be a policeman.

36:38.446 --> 36:39.989
| want to get answers.

36:42.992 --> 36:45.912
Why did you ask me
about boyfriends?

36:46.037 --> 36:47.122
Because | thought you were lying

36:47.205 --> 36:48.581
about staying with a
school friend.

36:52.127 --> 36:53.128
| was.

36:56.256 --> 37:00.009
I'm going to wash my face
and change out of this.

37:00.135 --> 37:03.263
At least | won't look stupid
while I'm explaining about that.

37:08.893 --> 37:10.353
-[ GUNSHOT]
- [ BULLET CASING CLATTERS ]

37:11.896 --> 37:13.732
- [ GUNSHOT ]
- FRANK: Left-handed assailant.

37:15.024 --> 37:17.068
-[ GUNSHOT ]
- Critical shot.

37:17.193 --> 37:18.194
[ CONTINUES FIRING ]

37:22.365 --> 37:23.366
Nice.

37:24.159 --> 37:25.160
Again.

37:33.418 --> 37:35.336
| didn't stay
with a friend.

37:36.880 --> 37:38.339
| don't have any friends.

37:40.467 --> 37:43.261
| went into Dublin
and stayed in a hostel.

37:44.345 --> 37:45.889
The cheapest one
| could find.

37:47.098 --> 37:48.141
Why?

37:49.392 --> 37:51.352
Jessica started her period.

37:52.979 --> 37:56.441
She doesn't understand
how to...

37:57.192 --> 37:59.110
look after herself.

37:59.819 --> 38:00.904
So...

38:01.446 --> 38:02.864
| doit.

38:02.989 --> 38:06.367
She's my sister,
and | love her.

38:06.451 --> 38:09.537
But | suppose I...
| just snapped.

38:10.872 --> 38:15.251
So | stayed in a hostel
with these damp beds

38:15.376 --> 38:18.004
and mad people
screaming at each other,

38:18.129 --> 38:20.840
and in the day,
| walked around.

38:20.965 --> 38:23.009
And then | went home
and got on with things.

38:24.469 --> 38:25.887
That's it.

38:26.304 --> 38:27.806
So pathetic.

38:28.348 --> 38:29.808
No, it isn't.

38:32.977 --> 38:35.438
I'm so sorry
about your friend.

38:36.523 --> 38:38.983
And I'm so sorry
about your sister.

38:45.657 --> 38:47.450
RECORDED VOICE: Doors opening.

39:00.255 --> 39:02.131
- Where are you going?
- Home.

39:02.257 --> 39:04.217
You seen the time?

39:04.342 --> 39:06.177
And, O'Kelly's waiting
for you.

39:10.223 --> 39:12.183
RECORDED VOICE: Doors closing.

39:14.227 --> 39:16.020
Who do you reckon
chucked who?

39:17.522 --> 39:19.399
| think Reilly dumped her.

39:19.524 --> 39:21.901
She got stars in her eyes,
and he gave it the old...

39:22.026 --> 39:23.152
[ WHISTLES ]

39:24.404 --> 39:25.405
What's the matter with you?

39:26.573 --> 39:29.033
I'm bored of you
talking shit, Quigley.

39:35.415 --> 39:36.583
[ SIGHS ]

39:46.050 --> 39:48.469
Most of my day has been
spent taking calls,

39:48.595 --> 39:51.431
asking me why my lead detective
on Operation Vestal

39:51.556 --> 39:54.142
told a journalist
to fuck off on tape.

39:56.978 --> 39:58.021
You can tell him to fuck off

39:58.146 --> 39:59.439
whenever you like,
but not on tape.

39:59.606 --> 40:00.398
Not on a case like this.

40:00.523 --> 40:02.901
It looks like
we're not doing our jobs.

40:03.026 --> 40:05.028
He's getting a campaign
going now, to find Adam

40:05.153 --> 40:06.571
because we haven't
managed it.

40:06.654 --> 40:08.239
Well, good luck to him.

40:10.033 --> 40:11.326
Adam's dead.

40:12.368 --> 40:13.578
What?

40:15.622 --> 40:19.042
Had it confirmed last hour.

40:19.125 --> 40:20.293
Wrapped his car
around a tree

40:20.418 --> 40:22.128
in some remote town
in New Zealand.

40:22.629 --> 40:24.213
Couple of years ago.

40:24.339 --> 40:25.298
Well...

40:27.675 --> 40:29.969
That's pissed on his
campaign chips, huh?

40:30.511 --> 40:32.055
Yeah.

40:32.180 --> 40:34.223
So what have
you got, Detective?

40:34.349 --> 40:35.934
Because right now,
you don't have anything

40:36.059 --> 40:38.394
apart from a bunch of people
telling the same story

40:38.519 --> 40:40.229
they've been telling
for over 20 years.

40:40.355 --> 40:41.105
It's stalemate.

40:41.230 --> 40:42.607
It's all about
finding Shane Waters.

40:42.732 --> 40:44.400
That'll break Jonathan
and Margaret

40:44.525 --> 40:46.152
Devlin and give us
Katy's killer.

40:46.361 --> 40:48.404
You're pinning everything
on a homeless man

40:48.529 --> 40:52.283
who's most likely an addict
with mental health issues,

40:52.408 --> 40:55.620
who is going to get rinsed in
court as an unreliable witness.

40:55.745 --> 40:57.538
- You need more.
- | know.

40:59.207 --> 41:00.249
[ SIGHS ]

41:03.544 --> 41:05.588
It's probably the first thing
you thought,

41:05.713 --> 41:07.256
the first thing you saw.

41:07.382 --> 41:09.342
You've probably
already got it,

41:09.467 --> 41:11.094
the key to it all.

41:11.219 --> 41:13.304
So, go back.
Go back over everything.

41:13.429 --> 41:15.515
- | have been.
- Go back again.

41:16.641 --> 41:19.227
But first, go home
and get some sleep.

41:19.352 --> 41:22.188
Come on, son.
| have faith in you, huh.

41:26.442 --> 41:28.403
[ OPENS DOOR ]

41:28.528 --> 41:30.405
Was it accidental
or deliberate?

41:31.030 --> 41:32.240
Adam?

41:34.742 --> 41:38.371
Officially, an accident,
but it reads deliberate.

41:39.539 --> 41:41.082
Christ.

41:42.250 --> 41:43.668
The fucking case.

41:48.131 --> 41:49.424
[ LIGHT BUZZING ]

42:04.355 --> 42:05.606
[ MUNCHING ]

